The paper deals with channel state information in massive MIMO networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of orthogonal pilot sequences is a common technique in wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also focuses on the performance analysis of massive MIMO networks, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM).
